headline: Assessing FICO’s Value After 23.7% Drop and Recent Fintech Partnerships in 2025
summary: Ever wondered if Fair Isaac’s recent price swings mean now is a great time to buy or if the stock might be overvalued? Let’s dig into why this company has caught the market’s attention. Fair Isaac shares have seen big gains in the past, up an impressive 277.6% over five years, but have dropped 23.7% in the last year, suggesting a shift in investor sentiment. Major headlines lately have focused on Fair Isaac’s partnerships with fintech firms and an industry-wide push towards AI-driven credit...
